President Trump spoke in the Diplomatic Reception Room about the progress being made on constructing a border wall in El Paso, Texas. He emphasized the need for a wall to prevent criminals, drug dealers, and gang members from entering the country. The President also expressed his concerns about the release of criminals into American communities and the dangers of human smuggling. Several sheriffs expressed their support for the President's efforts to secure the border and maintain funding for ICE. The President praised the work of ICE and criticized the Democrats for wanting to cut its funding. He concluded by stating that the possibility of another government shutdown depends on the Democrats.